 The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) has released the list of shortlisted candidates for the final screening of qualified candidates for the narcotic officer and narcotic assistant cadres. The screening exercise was suspended in January due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Director, Media & Advocacy, NDLEA Headquarters, Abuja, Femi Babafemi, in a statement on Saturday said the screening will now proceed in batches in designated centres. For NDLEA headquarters, Abuja, Babafemi said candidates within the following categories and whose names are listed on the final list as published on the Agency’s website: www.ndlea.gov.ng should report at NDLEA headquarters at No 6 Port Harcourt Crescent, Off Gimbiya Street, Area 11, Garki, Abuja. They are to report as follows: a. Lawyers 17th May, 2021 b. Specialised Courses and Languages 19th May, 2021 c. Special Skill Candidates – 20th May, 2021 d. Doctors – 21st May, 2021 For the NDLEA Academy, Jos, Plateau State, he said candidates on the general list should report at the Agency’s Academy, Katon Rikkos, Jos, Plateau State for screening in the order of batches specified below: a. BATCH A: Nos 1- 242 (17th May, 2021) b. BATCH B: Nos 243- 484 (18th May, 2021) c. BATCH C: Nos 485-726 (19th May, 2021) d. BATCH D: Nos 727 968 (20th May, 2021) e. BATCH E: Nos 969 1209 (21st May, 2021) f. BATCH F: Nos 1210- 1450 (22nd May, 2021)  For the Narcotic Assistant cadre, he said candidates should report at the Agency’s Academy, Katon Rikkos, Jos, Plateau State for screening in strict compliance to the order specified below between 24th May 8th June 2021. The order are as follows a. BATCH A: Nos 1 300 (24th May, 2021) b. BATCH B: Nos 301 600 (25th May, 2021) c. BATCH C: Nos 601 900 (26th May, 2021) d. BATCH D: Nos 901 -1,200 (27th May, 2021) e. BATCH E: Nos 1,201 1,500 (28th May, 2021) f. BATCH F: Nos 1,501 1,800 (29th May, 2021) g. BATCH G: Nos 1,801 2,100 (31st May, 2021) h. BATCH H: Nos 2,101 2,400 (1st June, 2021) i. BATCH I: Nos 2,401 2,700 (2nd June, 2021) j. BATCH J: Nos 2,701 3,000 (3rd June, 2021) k. BATCH K: 3,001 – 3,300 (4th June, 2021) l. BATCH L: Nos 3,301 3,600 (5th June, 2021) m. BATCH M: Nos 3,601 – 3,900 (7th June, 2021) n. BATCH N: Nos 3,901 4,165 (8th June, 2021). Babafemi said candidates attending the screening exercise must strictly observe the COVID-19 non-pharmaceutical protocol and arrive at the designated venue on the specified date. The candidates were also directed to present their guarantors form, original and duplicate copies of their academic credentials, birth certificates, proof of state of origin and certificate of medical fitness from a Government Hospital. Also required from them were a pair apiece of shorts and round neck white T-shirt as well as canvas and stockings. Any candidate who fails to abide by any of the conditions would be disqualified instantly, the statement stressed. 